  "text": "whereas the deepening of the CCD [CITATION_1] happens closer to the Lutetian-Bartonian limit (Fig. 16 ). These two parameters should theoretically have the same and contemporaneous response to change in ice storage. However, these two curves were established in two different domains, i.e. in the western Atlantic and in the Pacific and dating methods were different in the two cases. We could reasonably conclude that the rapid deepening of the CCD and the sea-level reflect the same event. . Sedimentologic sections studied in the Lutetian (L1 to L5) and Bartonian (B1 to B5) sections. Geographic and stratigraphic locations of the sections are reported in Fig. 2 and Fig. 14 respectively. Variations of the accommodation have been calculated estimating paleobathymetries from facies models established in this study [CITATION_2] for Lutetian and Bartonian sediments respectively (see attached Tables 1 and 2 for the correspondence between facies code and bathymetry).",
